    <!-- Athletic Body Type Diet Plan -->
    <h2>Athletic Body Type for Females</h2>

    <h3>Body Type Description</h3>
    <p>Athletic females often have a muscular build, broader shoulders, and a narrow waist. They may have a lower body fat percentage and a well-defined physique due to regular physical activity. This body type can include various variations such as mesomorphs, who easily build muscle, and ectomorphs, who may have a leaner frame but are still active.</p>

    <h3>Food List for Athletic Females</h3>
    <p>To support an active lifestyle and muscle maintenance, a balanced diet rich in whole foods is essential. The recommended macronutrient breakdown for athletic females is generally 40% carbs, 30% protein, and 30% fat.</p>

    <h4>Meat and Fish</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>Chicken breast</li>
        <li>Lean beef</li>
        <li>Salmon</li>
        <li>Tuna</li>
        <li>Eggs</li>
        <li>Turkey</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Dairy</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>Greek yogurt</li>
        <li>Cottage cheese</li>
        <li>Milk (low-fat or whole)</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Fruits and Vegetables</h4>
